                  <interp inst="t18190707-85-crimeloc467" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18190707-85-off464 t18190707-85-crimeloc467"></join>. On the 23d of June, at seven o'clock in the evening, I was coming home, and saw the prisoner come out of my shop, with a rug under his arm. I pursued him. The moment he saw me he quickened his pace; I lost sight of him for a minute, he then dropped the rug. He was running along Kendall's-mews. I picked up the rug, and called Stop thief! he was stopped in my sight - they let him go. I pursued him again and secured him; he said he was very sorry.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner. It is my first offence.</p>
